net.antoniy.beacon
Interface BeaconParams

public interface BeaconParams

BeaconParams is used to store initialization parameters for the Beacon service.

Author:
Antoniy Chonkov

getBeaconTimeout

int getBeaconTimeout()
Retrieve beacon service timeout value. This value indicates how much time should pass before an active device that doesn't broadcast UDP datagrams should be considered inactive.

Returns:
the timeout value in milliseconds.

setBeaconTimeout

void setBeaconTimeout(int beaconTimeout)
Set the beacon service timeout value. This value indicates how much time should pass before an active device that doesn't broadcast UDP datagrams should be considered inactive.

Parameters:
beaconTimeout - the timeout value in milliseconds.

getDataMaxSize

int getDataMaxSize()
Retrieves the max size of the broadcasting meta data.

Returns:
the max size of the meta data that is broadcasting.

setDataMaxSize

void setDataMaxSize(int dataMaxSize)
Set maximum size of the broadcast meta data. The generated JSON meta data will be validated against this value. Should be > 0 and < 65535. The default value is optimal size to use with UDP datagrams.

Default: 512 bytes

Parameters:
dataMaxSize - the max size of the meta data in bytes.
